Subject:    sri-nic ...in-addr.arpa domains?
From:       <a href="?a=95837785400014&r=1&w=2">"Stuart Levy" &lt;slevy () uc ! msc ! umn ! edu&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198811">1988-11-26 22:18:06</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837783027032&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837783027032&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

In playing with nslookup this evening I noticed something odd.
Querying sri-nic (and gunter-adam) with QCLASS=IN, QTYPE=NS
for the servers for various in-addr.arpa zones, I was surprised to see...
nothing, just another &gt; prompt.  Looking further, it seems those two
servers are returning the answers in the AUTHORITY section.

Yet when I ask about other domains, e.g. umn.edu or uiuc.edu, those same
servers return the answers in both the AUTHORITY and ADDITIONAL sections.

This isn't causing any problem, but I'm curious about two things:
  - what's different to cause one kind of response for IN-ADDR.ARPA zones
      and another for other zones?
  - why aren't those NS RR's showing up in the ANSWER section, for Pete's sake?

	Stuart Levy

